// Fixture for task 4132: exercises default-solver auto-resolution via `reify eval`.
//
// AutoMinimize has one auto param `thickness` (no default), a single upper-bound
// constraint (thickness < 20mm), and a structure-level `minimize thickness`
// objective.  When the default DimensionalSolver is wired into cmd_eval the
// resolution phase runs Nelder-Mead and pushes thickness toward the natural
// lower bound (~1 micron), printing a numeric SI value ≤ 5 mm instead of `undef`.
//
// A single upper-bound constraint is used intentionally (no lower-bound constraint)
// to avoid floating-point boundary issues at the lower bound — the same design
// as crates/reify-eval/tests/resolution.rs:876 (e2e_minimize_through_real_solver).
structure AutoMinimize {
    param thickness: Length = auto

    constraint thickness < 20mm

    minimize thickness
}
